main event: Civilians in Frankfort, Kentucky observed a bright yellow light in the sky during the early hours of April 1, 1968.
interesting points: The observers were awakened by a loud noise similar to power lines on a cold day., The object was described as a dull yellowish light that moved for about five minutes., Dogs were barking and appeared frightened during the sighting., There is insufficient data to draw any conclusions about the object., A form was sent to the observer but was not returned for further investigation.
sighted object: A bright yellow light in the sky
witness description: Civilians who were asleep before being awakened by the noise.
